encspot (2.01+mtn20110307) unstable; urgency=low

  * Regression fix. The original EncSpot code used the BOOL type
    (actually an int) to store the scale factor. When the code was refactored
    to use the true bool type, scale factor calculation broke.
  * Fixed use of "\r\n" as line ending, which is invalid under both
    Windows and *nix since "\n" is automatically converted to the native
    platform's line ending.
  * Fixes to compilation warnings observed under Ubuntu 10.04.
  * Minor update to manual page.

 -- Francis Russell <francis@unchartedbackwaters.co.uk>  Mon, 07 Mar 2011 11:06:01 +0000

encspot (2.01+mtn20110228) unstable; urgency=low

  * General code cleanup:
    - Use C99 types instead of Windows ones.
    - Compilation warning fixes.
    - Improved itoa replacement.
    - Unused code removal.
    - Fixes to incorrect use of unsigned arithmetic.
  * Print the exceptions thrown by EncSpot.
  * Update standards version.
  * Switch to debhelper automatic scripts. 

